.TH GIT\-NOTE\-COMMIT 1 "2026-03-01" "git-issue 1.0.0-rc1" "Git Issue Tracker"
.SH NAME
git\-note\-commit \- attach issue notes to git commits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git\-note\-commit
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manages structured notes on git commits, linking commits to issues
and recording developer thoughts.
Notes are stored using git's built-in notes system
.RB ( git\-notes (1)).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "add " "commit issue " [ thoughts ]
Attach a note to
.IR commit .
.I issue
is one or more issue references (e.g.,
.BR #102 ,
.BR "#103,#211" ).
.I thoughts
is an optional free-text annotation.
Appends to existing notes if the commit already has one.
.TP
.B list
List commits that have notes.
.TP
.BI "show " commit
Print the note attached to
.IR commit .
.TP
.B template
Print a template for manual use with
.BR "git notes add" .
.SH NOTE FORMAT
.nf
Issue: #102
Thoughts: Started session management implementation
Date: 2026-03-01 12:00:00
Author: Jane Doe
.fi
.PP
Multiple notes on the same commit are separated by
.BR \-\-\- .
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
git\-note\-commit add HEAD '#102' 'Began OAuth2 work'
git\-note\-commit add abc123 '#103,#211' 'RBAC affects admin pages'
git\-note\-commit show HEAD
git\-note\-commit list
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-notes (1)
